TRAN HOANG SON is a Junior Test Engineer with approximately 2.41 years of commercial experience. Their core expertise lies in Black Box Testing, White Box Testing, API Testing, and SDLC/STLC methodologies using Selenium, JUnit, Cucumber, and Appium frameworks. They have worked on multiple projects, including a 6-month stint as a QA Analyst at Superfine, where they developed automation scripts using Java and Selenium, and proposed UI/UX improvements. Additionally, they have 18 months of experience as a Software Tester/QC at DXC Viet Nam, where they collaborated with developers to create effective test scripts, worked with Product Owners to clarify requirements, and defined automation test scripts for API testing using Java and JUnit.

Technically, they are proficient in Java, SQL, and have hands-on experience with tools like Jira, Git, and Postman. Their expertise extends to various testing techniques, including Functional Testing, GUI Testing, Regression Testing, Retesting, Integration Testing, System Testing, and User Acceptance Testing (UAT). They are also familiar with Agile Scrum methodologies, BDD, Test Time Estimation, Defect Tracking, Version Control, and UI/UX Improvement. With a strong foundation in Software Engineering, having graduated from TON DUC THANG UNIVERSITY, and certified in ISTQB Certified Tester Foundation Level and ISTQB Certified - Agile Tester, TRAN HOANG SON possesses a unique blend of technical and domain knowledge, making them a valuable asset in the field of software testing and quality assurance.